node.text:
Brunch without weed is just a sad breakfast 💫

..swipe for a melt shot 😛

I went all out with this one, because who doesn't love a good brunch? 
Used my cannabis and black truffle olive oil made with my @levo_oil machine to make a lil hollandaise 😇 

Everyone likes to make infused sweets, but where's some love for the savories? In my opinion, it's an herb that should also be used for its flavor -- just like any other garden variety. 

Friends, today I present to you an english muffin with melted alp wildflower cheese, raspberry habanero jelly, microgreens, applewood smoked lamb bacon, a poached duck egg, my infused hollandaise, and some edible gold flakes for good measure. The wildflower cheese, jelly, and microgreens helped to cut through the heaviness of the infused oil and rich duck egg, balancing the herbal tones and fat for a perfect blend. I will say, my first holladaise recipe came out a lot better the first time consistency-wise, but I added some extra chili powder to it this time and the kick was very welcomed. Overall, I'm really happy with this meal, so much that I made seconds and then thirds 🙈

The @levo_oil infuser made all of this extremely easy from start to finish. I made the olive oil days ago using cannabis nugs, dried black truffles, and organic olive oil. All I had to do was pack the little pod (almost like a reusable keurig container), set my time and temp, and then it did all of the messy parts for me... aka more time to consume my favorites 😉 As you all know, I hate straining and dealing with a cannabis mess. As some of you may NOT know, I'm actually topically allergic to cannabis. I break out in mild hives with contact. Because of this, the Levo has made my life a lot easier because I'm not as involved with the infusing process and I cannot be more thankful for that lol.

Anyway, I would post a recipe but like... I gave you all of the ingredients already and eggs benny is eggs benny. If anyone wants any pointers on how to poach an egg or the base for my hollandaise I will happily answer in the comments 😘

node.text: a dab to match my mood 👑

Hashy Sunday, y’all 💫

I say this a lot, because it’s true, but I really do have so many projects I’m currently working on ☠️ The bags under my eyes prove it lol. Last month I switched jobs and am now (very happily) working 50-60 hour weeks between this new one and my other work. This is my first day off in over 3 weeks, and I really should be working on some things today too 😅 Just wanted to pop by and update y’all since my account was disabled for a while. 

All of my projects and work involve cannabis, so I’m happy for when I can finally share 🙈🌈🔥

node.text:
balanced breakfast ☯️

this is one of my favorites I ever made. 2 different types of purple kief (and it took way too long to make this design with it). I’ve only attempted the yin yang twice and I think I peaked with this one lol. Hence I like to bring it back on my page every now and then.

I like taking the time to make these for a few reasons. Mainly, I just like to make things. Nothing exists in that moment except what you’re working on. A balance between what’s going on in my mind and putting it into my hands. Even if it’s just a bowl pack that I’ll spark and burn afterward. Which is my second favorite part after creating things. There’s something so freeing about the temporary state of it, so I love smoking the creations shortly after I make them. Is that weird?

Anyway, there’s your daily dose of dubs high thoughts lol. 

New tings soon 🤫
